<paragraph id="8BD436C28715AA0A46A0FD31D805AE66" blockId="14.[189,1399,707,1091]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Cockerell described this subspecies apparently based on a single female specimen collected by the American entomologist and naturalist Charles Thomas Brues (
<date id="FFD510028715AA0A4584FD15DF42A927" box="[921,1058,743,770]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1879" valueMax="1955">1879–1955</date>
), specialist on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D418715AA0A42D2FD1ADA75A900" authority=", Diptera" authorityName="Diptera" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera, Diptera</taxonomicName>
and on insect diet (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B338715AA0A47EBFCF9D90AA903" author="Salt" box="[502,618,779,806]" firstAuthor="Salt" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="628" refId="ref21864" refString="Salt G. 1955. Prof. C. T. Brues. Nature 176: 628. https: // doi. org / 10.1038 / 176628 a 0" type="journal article" year="1955">Salt 1955</bibRefCitation>
), during a trip to South America. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B338715AA0A45F3FCF9DFB2A900" author="Moure" box="[1006,1234,779,805]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Moure" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref21502" refString="Moure J. S., Melo G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure J. S., Urban D. &amp; Melo G. A. R. (orgs) Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region: 83 - 142. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitibrazil." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B91FEAD08715AA0A425EFCFEDF1DA900" box="[1091,1149,779,805]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that it was described from 
<typeStatus id="54D088608715AA0A47D6FCDDD955A96C" box="[459,565,815,841]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">syntypes</typeStatus>
. Nevertheless, only a single female with original Cockerell’s label of “type” was found at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE078715AA0A47ADFCA1D96EA948" box="[432,526,851,877]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
. Due to the lack of evidence on the existence of more type specimens and the impossibility to deduce this fact from the original description, the female housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE078715AA0A42DAFC84DE41A9B5" box="[1223,1313,886,912]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
is here interpreted as 
<typeStatus id="54D088608715AA0A477EFC6BDAADA996" box="[355,461,921,947]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
, taking into account the information of the Cockerell’s own label. The specimen (
<figureCitation id="13502A478715AA0A46DBFC4FDA6DA9F2" box="[198,269,957,983]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1468,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[189,1398,1468,1923]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. Centris nitida geminata Cockerell, 1914, holotype, ♀ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534196). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722968/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) has the following data label: Guayaquil. 
<collectingCountry id="F37C76528715AA0A4518FC4FD809A9F2" box="[773,873,957,983]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, May-June 1913. C. T. Brues [printed]\ [red label] Type No [printed] 54855 [handwritten] USNM [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D418715AA0A45CFFC13DE51A9DE" authority="Ckll" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1914" box="[978,1329,993,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitida" subSpecies="geminata">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD08715AA0A45CFFC13DF92A9DE" box="[978,1266,993,1019]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Centris nitida geminata</emphasis>
Ckll
</taxonomicName>
